            <div type="translation" resp="#jmr" xml:lang="en">
               <p>To Mistress Caelestis, for the welfare of Emperors <supplied reason="lost">Marcus A</supplied>urelius
            Antoninus and Marcus Aurelius Commodus, Augusti, <del rend="erasure"><supplied reason="lost">and Crispina Augusta</supplied>
            <gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="line"/></del>; Lucius Aemilius Calpurnianus Muse and his wife, Mucia Pudentilla, gave and
            dedicated <supplied reason="subaudible">this</supplied> on account of the honours paid to Lucius Aemilius
            Mucianus and Quintus Aemilius Augurinus, formerly their most dutiful sons.</p></div>
         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en">
            <p>For Lady Caelestis, for the safety of the emperors Marcus Aurelius Antoninus [[and Marcus Aurelius Commodus]], Augusti, [[and Bruttia Crispina, Augusta]]; 
               Lucius Aemilius Calprurnius Muse and Mucia Pudentilla, his  <supplied reason="subaudible">wife</supplied> gave and dedicated <supplied reason="subaudible">this</supplied> 
               on account of the honours paid to Lucius Aemilius
               Mucianus and Quintus Aemilius Augurinus, formerly their most dutiful sons.</p>
         </div>
         
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Line 4: Commodus' name was erased after his death in 192 but reinserted later. Commodus was Augustus with his father from 177 to l80. </p>
           <!--  <p>Line 6: Alföldy's restoration is based on a re-examination of the stone</p> -->
         </div>
